# Frontend UI Style Guide

## No Rounded Corners

This project uses **sharp/square corners**. Do NOT add `rounded`, `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`, `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-3xl`, or `border-radius` to UI elements.

Exceptions (the ONLY cases where rounded is allowed):
- `rounded-full` for avatars, circular indicator dots, spinners, and badges that must be circular

```html
<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<div class="bg-white shadow-md p-4 rounded-lg">
<button class="bg-indigo-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md">

<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<div class="bg-white shadow-md p-4">
<button class="bg-indigo-500 text-white px-4 py-2">

<!-- ✅ OK — circular avatar -->
<img class="rounded-full" />
```

## Color Palette

- Primary: indigo (`bg-indigo-500`, `hover:bg-indigo-600`, `text-indigo-500`)
- Accent: blue (`bg-blue-500`, `text-blue-500`)
- Neutral: gray (`bg-gray-50/100/200`, `text-gray-400/500/600`, `border-gray-300`)
- Background: white (`bg-white`)
- Gradients (header/footer): `bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-indigo-600`
- Custom: `text-if` (#fc6396), `text-sf` (#52c3ef)

## Typography

- Headings: `font-poppins`
- Body: `font-inter`
- Code/solutions: `font-mono`

## Buttons

Primary button style (see `components/button/primary.vue`):
- `bg-indigo-500 hover:bg-indigo-600 active:bg-indigo-700 text-white px-4 py-2`
- Shadow: `shadow-md hover:shadow-lg`
- Hover lift: `hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:scale-105`
- No border-radius

Inline/small buttons:
- `bg-indigo-500 hover:bg-opacity-90 text-white px-2 py-1`

## Cards & Containers

- `bg-white shadow-md p-4` — no rounded corners
- Border accents: `border-l-2 md:border-l-4 border-blue-500`
- Dividers: `border-t border-gray-300`

## Form Inputs

- `block w-full shadow-sm border-gray-300`
- Focus: `focus:ring-2 focus:border-indigo-300 focus:ring-indigo-200/50`
- No border-radius

## General Patterns

- Framework: Nuxt 3 + Tailwind CSS (with `@tailwindcss/forms` base strategy)
- Dark mode via `@nuxtjs/color-mode` — `.dark` class on `<html>`, system preference auto-detect
- Global dark overrides in `assets/css/tailwind.css` handle `bg-white`, `bg-gray-*`, `text-gray-*`, `border-gray-*` automatically
- For new components: prefer global overrides; add `dark:` utility only when the global rule doesn't cover the case (e.g. header/nav with custom indigo backgrounds)
- Use `useColorMode()` composable for programmatic access
- Shadows for depth: `shadow-sm` (inputs), `shadow-md` (cards), `shadow-lg` (dropdowns)
- Transitions: `transition-all duration-200 ease-in-out`
- Icons: Iconify via `<Icon name="..." />`
- No UI component library — all custom components
